ScheduleItem.Synopsis: Sixteen strangers head back to summer camp to relive the most magical time of their lives. From the ugly duckling turned fashion model, to the nerdy Eagle Scout looking to show the world what geeks can do, to the Miami firefighter who grew up pranking girls, all of these campers came to play. And this time around they’ll be competing against each other in a summer-long “Battle of the Sexes” for a $250,000 prize.

After first round elimination votes are announced, the men believe there is a rat among them! With one rogue vote, suspicions grow about who went behind the group’s back. Summer romance ignites between campers at the poolside weekly camp social. Camp counselor elections get heated when there’s a tie and one camper betrays the other to win the title. This week’s color war is s’more inspired. In the end, another camper is sent packing.

A young high school male comes in to the hospital with a lethal poisoning, but neither House nor the rest of his team can figure out what has caused it. House decides to send Cameron and Chase to the teen's home to find the hot new drug House is sure he's taking. They don't find drugs, but they do find something that would explain his symptoms. That is, until another student comes in with the exact same symptoms. Meanwhile, an 82-year-old patient becomes obsessed with House, who is trying to figure out the basis of her renewed fascination with her sexual feelings.

RACHEL, a young girl from the Midwest who moved to NYC, is murdered after visiting a medical center to receive treatment for an assault. MAYA, a nurse’s aid from the medical center and her boyfriend DAMON, engage in a series of sexual assaults and murders. They are responsible for Rachel’s death among others. Nichols and Stevens must figure out if RANDALL, another nurse’s aid or Maya and Damon are the killers before there is another murder. The crux of the investigation lies in uncovering the psyches of Maya and Randall as individuals and as a couple.

ScheduleItem.Synopsis: Tutuola is reunited with his own son, as he risks his life to save two small children: one who is caught in the middle of a bodega robbery, and the other from the junkie who set the child's mother up for murder and then stole him to use as a front in her scheme to boost materials for her meth lab.

ScheduleItem.Synopsis: The discovery of the bodies of two young gay men, who were both meth addicts and victims of a new strain of AIDS that can kill its victims in less than a year, leads to an investigation. Tutuola learns that his son, Ken, is gay and has difficulty accepting it.

ScheduleItem.Synopsis: An unwelcome surprise has Connor hunting a mole at V3. Dani counsels an accountant with a big secret. Paloma wants to get on the fast track. TK's new relationship with Sheera heats up.
A well-known Las Vegas humanitarian is killed for her involvement in a dog-fighting ring, and CSI searches for clues in the strip club murder that Warrick was framed for.
When the CSI team investigates the brutal murder of a family, they trace the killer to the house next door, which might belong to the "Dr. Jekyll" serial killer.
